Packages
A collection of files that make up an application 
It contains data/metadata about the application 

-Package description
-version
-Dependencies

Package Manager
-installs, Upgrades and removes packages
-Manages dependancies
-Keep track of what is installed


The package manager uses the metadata to auomatically install any required dependancies 


Installng software on RPM Distros
RPM Redhat Package Manager
-Redhat
-CentOS
-Fedora
-Oracle linux
-Scientfic linux


Yum 
The Yum command line utility is a package manager

Yum search string ->search for string
yum info [package] ->Display info
yum install [-y] package ->install package
yum remove package   ->remove package



rpm 
rpm -qa list all installed packages
rpm -qf /pathto/file List the file's package

rpm -ql package list packages files
rpm -ivh package.rpm install package
rpm -e package Erase (unistall) package

Example
install yum search inkscape
yum info inkscape-docs
yum info inkscape  -> Graphics editor
su - -> root user
yum install inkscape
yum install -y gimp
yum remove gimp -y


Install software not included in the package manager
Downloade directly from the site
rpm -q
rpm -qa | sort | less


Installing software on DEB Distros
-Debian
-Linux mint
-Ubuntu

APT _ Advanced Packaging TOol
apt -cache search string Search for string.
apt-get install [-y] package install package.

apt-get remove package Remove package, leaving configuration
apt-get purge package Remove package, deleting configuration
apt-cache Show package Display Information about package 

dpkg -l - list installed packages
dpkg -S /path/to/file List file's package.
dpkg -L package List all files in package.
dpkg -i package.deb Install package.

Example 
apt-cache search inkscape
sudo apt-get install inkscape 

Summary 
RPM
-yum
-rpm
